            "subject": "LU-4647 nodemap: fix problem with node reclassification"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Alexey Lyashkov",
          "email": "alexey_lyashkov@xyratex.com",
          "date": "2014-11-02 16:53:48.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-12-04 17:53:02.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-5581 ldlm: evict clients returning errors on ASTs",
        "message": "LU-5581 ldlm: evict clients returning errors on ASTs\n\nWhen a client returns an error other then EINVAL replying to blocking\nast, it is unsafe to cancel the lock on server side only, because the\nclient may continue its I/O assuming it still owns the lock while the\nreal lock may be granted already to another client.\n\nIn only valid error case when client replied to AST with EINVAL cancel\nthe lock and return ERESTART, evict the client in any other error\ncase.\n\nXyratex-bug-id: MRP-2041\nSigned-off-by: Alexey Lyashkov <alexey_lyashkov@xyratex.com>\nChange-Id: Ibce60ce3b2c24ba388155ac49cba8f20388893e7\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/11752\nTested-by: Jenkins\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@gmail.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
